<item>
            <title>[LU-1073] mandatory (LOCK_MAND) flock requests cause unknown fcntl lock type: 32 Lustre error messages</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1073</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;running samba (or any application which uses LOCK_MAND) on Lustre floods system log with error messages:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;LustreError: 13022:0:(file.c:2044:ll_file_flock()) unknown fcntl lock type: 32&lt;br/&gt;
LustreError: 13022:0:(file.c:2044:ll_file_flock()) Skipped 746 previous similar messages&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment>samba 3.6.x running over Lustre fs.</environment>
        <key id="13109">LU-1073</key>
